snippet.textDisplay: First, To Every Front Line Worker, Thank You For Your Bravery, Your Life and Your Dedication! I was Diagnosed 2/2017 with Stage 4 NSCLC Metastatic, wasn't expected to survive, now Corvid19 is here, spreading like wild fire...and doctors already having to choose who lives and who dies...chilling. I know my end, but, for those of you who still have a choice, I sincerely hope you choose wisely and Stay Home! I have two rounds of Chemo for April and I am not afraid, what I am concerned about is this, YOU! Should I get Corvid19, the chances are I may not get a Ventilator due to the Cancer....what saddens me is how precious each and every Life is and how many are doing what they want rather than whats best. Gov of Colorado calls this Virus The Grimm Reaper, it don't care who it takes out! So many dying Alone, no one to hold his or her hand as They Take Their Last Breath, no one to say Good Bye too, no one to say I Love You Too, No One, they Die Alone. Living and Breathing are Priceless Gifts please don't throw them away because You Don't Want To Stay Home! I listen to my Cancer Doctor, this is not going away anytime soon, this is Reality folks. I am not Pleading for my own life, I am Pleading For Yours, nothing is more important on the face of this earth Than You Living and Breathing, nothing! PLEASE, Follow Instructions and Stay Home! PLEASE, You Living and Breathing means so much to me, I only hope it does to you too!
